<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 25 at 3:31PM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...INCREASED FIRE DANGER SATURDAY AFTERNOON AND EVENING...
Westerly winds of 10 to 20 mph with gusts of 30 mph, combined
with relative humidity values below 30 percent will result in
increased fire danger across eastern Tennessee and southwest North
Carolina Saturday afternoon and evening. If you do burn, use
extreme caution since fires can quickly get out of hand under
these conditions.</description>
